Item: Primadonna Project Page for Studio Outreach
Additional notes/description: • Ko, Shru, Jackson waiting on to do studio outreach

• Flatten a 3d scene to a 2d b&w lineart image
• This is actually just Qwen style model guided img->img

2 approaches
• Background image PERSPECTIVE modification (more control, but maybe lower quality?)
    a. x, y, z point of reference
    b. roll, pitch, yaw rotation point of reference
• Apply a camera movement to a 2d image and genarate output video (less control, but maybe higher quality?)
    a. Bonus: supported modifications by prompts
    b. Bonus: generate as sequence of static images at defined time intervals
• _these are essentially the same thing, just like group 2, 2 different approaches to give workflows for for the same end goal_

• Change primary source of light/angle of light
    ◦ Bonus: Add one or more secondary light sources/strength_notes: kontext can probably do this with text, maybe higher quality for less precision than ic relight_
    ◦ _specific x,y,z coordinate for light area (?)_
• _Seems to involve training_

lets make char trains fast

    ◦ Nano Banana

Item: Background v1.2: Inpainting and decouple some functions in workflow
Additional notes/description:
• Add inpainting support
• Decouple upscale from the detail mode so that  output is always 2K, but we can programmatically upscale to 4K
• Remove color shift (filter node)
• [Stretch] Switch to tell the workflow to only return the masked area when inpainting (the rest is made transparent)

read up on tooncomposer, think about training methodologies we can use to increase the resolution - or other ways (VACE train, etc) to train recent video models like wan2.1/wan2.2 to the have anime-like sparse frames

Item: Kontext Based Magic Pen Workflow Improvement
Additional notes/description:
Building a new magic pen workflow that utilizes Flux Kontext at it's core.

<@U0798RS2ESX> to lead this initiative with guidance and support from <@U06L088EW7K>.

This initiative is open to potential departures from the current modal (loras, switching) - but also open to still using them - with creative liberty on use case and value to be provided by <@U06L088EW7K> throughout the research development process. There is also a goal to enable other optimizations (as listed in the relevant message) throughout the development of this workflow.
